The 2017 Equifax data breach was a major cybersecurity failure caused mainly by poor vulnerability management and delayed detection. Attackers exploited an unpatched Apache Struts vulnerability and gained access to highly sensitive consumer data. The breach affected millions of people and resulted in major financial, legal, and reputational consequences.
To prevent similar attacks, organizations must implement strong vulnerability management, continuous monitoring, encryption, network segmentation, and effective incident response planning. The Equifax breach remains an important lesson in the need for proactive cybersecurity governance and disciplined security operations.

